<Author>GP45
<Content>Perfect location We stayed one night here to celebrate the new year in London, watching the fireworks on the embankment as Big Ben struck. The hotel was in a perfect location for the underground. Having arrived at the hotel earlier than anticipated, our room was not quite ready. The receptionist was apologetic and helpful and we were provided with coffee while we waited. The room was spotless and quiet despite being in close proximity to the station. Our breakfast was good - plenty of choice and good coffee with attentive and polite staff. Overall, we had a very pleasant experience and check out at the end of our stay was no different. Smiling staff who made us feel like we mattered. For a hotel in the centre of London on new years eve, we thought the price reasonable. This was a very good place to stay and hopefully we will return! We can thoroughly recommend.GP. Solihull 
