<Author>douliou
<Content>Stylish, modern and friendly hotel, convenient location - great value for money! We stayed at the London Bridge Hotel from 4th-7th May. We chose the hotel based on the good reviews we'd seen and the excellent value rates we mnaged to find on the internet (拢249 BB for 3 nights).The location is really excellent - directy opposite a train/underground station which meant the rest of London was very accessible. However, the local area is well worth a scout if you have time - there are some great pubs along the river plus an excellent Italian restaurant (Strada) which has gorgeous views of the river. Borough Market and Vinopolis (a sort of wine museum) are within walking distance, also worth a visit, not to mention the London Dungeon, the Globe and the Tate Modern.Our room was a bit on the small side but think it was because there was a lot of furniture crammed in - including a HUGE bed! The bed was also very comfortable. The bathroom was a reasonable size with The White Company toiletries, which were a nice touch. It had all the mod cons e.g. hairdryer, iron, safe, tea/coffee making facilities. The decor was very modern and stylish.The hotel overall was very clean throughout. Our room and bathroom was always spotless.The breakfast was fine - usual Engish breakfast fare, plus continental breakfast selection, pastries, cereals etc. The breakfast staff were polite and friendly.The room service was excellent - it arrived very quickly and it was delicious. It also wasn't outrageously expensive, which is often the case with room service.The only problem we encountered was the temperature of the room - the first night it was stifling. When we spoke to Reception about it, they sent a maintenance engineer who arrived in minutes. The engineer fixed it within 15 mins - the room temperature became bearable and finally, very comfortable.Overall, I believe this hotel is excellent - the staff are polite and friendly, the hotel itself is very stylish, clean and comfortable. It 