<Content>Good Location and Very clean (new wing) We have just came home from a Easter weekend stay at The London Bridge Hotel. We stayed in an Executive Room in the 'new wing'. It was very clean and looked to be recently refurbished. It had a complimentary bottle each of still and sparkling mineral water replaced every day. The king size bed has a very firm mattress and is actually 2 twins joined together - you'd feel the join if you slept in the middle but there's enough room so this is not a problem.There is a large plasma TV with not many channels but Sky one and Sky sports and German mtv for some reason. We booked with a Continental breakfast which was sufficient for our needs.The hotel is right next door to London Bridge station. The hotel's website is not crystal clear on the location, so here's my tip: From the London Bridge Underground Station, follow signs for the London Bridge Main line train station on the upper level, then head for the exit between the London Bridge Bar and Boots Chemist, walk down the road past the 'All Bar One' bar, Fitness First Gym and then you'll reach the hotel.Others have talked about the nearby attractions but I would mention the 'Borough Market' which takes place on a Friday and Saturday. It has organic food and veg, olives, home made bread, cakes etc. - Not cheap but worth a visit. Check out visitsouthwark(-) for info on nearby places to visit, eat , drink etc. Also, don't forget to go for a walk on London Bridge itself for a great view of Tower Bridge and the Thames and to the area around 'Vinopolis' for a chilled out evening with a choice of nearby restaurants {Amano (Italian) Wagamama (Japanese)- both are recommended} and pubs too.The London Eye is a 15 minute walk from Waterloo station (2 stops from L Bridge)and definitely worth a visit. However, try and get there early (say around 9.30am) to avoid the massive queues for the tickets and thereafter the Eye itself.Overall, we had a great trip at a fantastic hotel and would de