<Content>Wonderful Location, Watch the "New" Wing Stayed at the London Bridge hotel July 15-20. Flew into LGW airport and took the train direct from the airport to London Bridge station. The hotel was a short 2 minute walk from the main entrance to the station.Hotel was very nice. Lobby was a bit small, but charming. Concierge desk was extremely helpful. Even recommended a launderette for us to do laundry! It's location made it easy to reach pretty much anywhere in London via the tube or train. Our particular room was in the new wing of the hotel. By new, they mean, recently acquired. It was a nice size, with plenty of room for our luggage and miscellaneous goods we collected while in London. Bed was comfy, bathroom was decent. Our only complaint was that the maid service did not replace our toiletries everyday. Also, the new wing is very inconveniently located from the lobby. You have to get to the first floor of the hotel, walk to the end of the halway (as if you were looking for a fire exit!), walk up a short flight of stairs, then board the miniscule lift to take you to your room. We did find a short cut, taking the lift down to the ground level, where the gym is located, and exiting out to the street from there. We tried to get back to our room the same way, and were successful, except our keycard did not call the lift, as they claimed it would. Instead, we had to walk up that short flight of stairs again in order to call the lift to our 3rd floor room!Other than those two complaints, we were extremely satisfied with our stay. Our rate included the English Breakfast buffet and was well worth it. Can't beat the location of the hotel and it's proximity to the London Bridge station. 
